      "span_text": "When genetic alterations such as L61P occur, they increase flexibility of the protein, as seen in MD simulations, which was suggested to be the cause of the disease. [CITATION_1] Although mutations may cause different diseases, the common trend is the same, namely, disease can be associated with a change in the conformational or dynamical properties of the corresponding protein (Table 4) .",
